ingredients: ["2 pkg. cream cheese", "1/4 c. crushed pineapple, drained", "1 pimento, cut fine", "2 Tbsp. pecans, chopped fine", "1 tsp. gelatin", "1 tsp. pineapple juice", "3 good firm green peppers, seeds removed"]
directions: ["Soak gelatin in the pineapple juice and dissolve over hot water.", "Add to pineapple and cream cheese mixture.", "Fill green peppers and set in refrigerator to harden.", "With a very sharp knife, cut the stuffed peppers crosswise into thin slices.", "Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise."]

title: Chocolate Chip Kiss Cookies
ingredients: ["1 (14 oz.) bag Hershey's Kisses with almonds", "2 c. softened margarine", "2/3 c. brown sugar", "2/3 c. granulated sugar", "2 tsp. vanilla", "4 c. flour", "2 c. mini chocolate chips", "Hershey's Chocolate Shoppe Topping (optional)"]
directions: ["Remove foil from Kisses.", "In a large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour; blend until smooth. Stir in chips. Mold scant tablespoon of dough around each Kiss, covering completely.", "Shape into ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.", "Cool.", "Remove from cookie sheet.", "Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies.", "Drizzle topping over each cookie (optional)."]

title: Hobo Bread
ingredients: ["3 c. self-rising flour", "1 tsp. sugar (heaping)", "1 can warm beer"]
directions: ["Mix; put in loaf pan.", "Bake for about 40 minutes at 300\u00b0. Serve warm."]

title: Chocolate Chip Butter Cookies
ingredients: ["2 sticks butter or margarine", "1 c. powdered sugar", "1/4 tsp. salt", "1 tsp. vanilla", "2 1/4 c. flour", "1 (6 oz.) pkg. semi-sweet chocolate chips"]
directions: ["Cream together oleo and sugar. Add salt, vanilla and flour. Mix until blended. Mixture will be stiff. Stir in chocolate chips. Roll into balls (3/4 inch) and flatten with a fork. Bake at 350\u00b0 about 12 to 13 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar."]

title: Creamy Honey Butter
ingredients: ["1/2 c. butter", "1/2 tsp. orange extract", "1/4 c. orange honey"]
directions: ["Beat butter until creamy and light. Add honey and orange extract and beat until fluffy. Taste at this point. If you like it sweeter, add a little more honey. Refrigerate."]
